# Login Debug & Fix Plan (502 Bad Gateway)

The user is unable to log in after deploying the Leave Tracker application. Investigation via the browser DOM and network logs shows a **502 Bad Gateway** error on `POST /api/auth/login`. This indicates that the Nginx reverse proxy (on `10.172.19.16`) cannot reach the backend service (proxied to `10.172.19.15:5000`).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Backend VM Architecture**: The current Nginx configuration assumes a 3-VM setup where the backend is on `10.172.19.15`. If you intended to run both frontend and backend on the same machine (`10.172.19.16`), we need to update the configuration to use `localhost:5000`.

> [!WARNING]
> **Port 5000 Accessibility**: Test-NetConnection to `10.172.19.15:5000` failed. This means either the service is not running on that VM or a firewall is blocking the traffic.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Verification Phase (Research)
- **Check Backend Process**: Verify if the backend service is running on `10.172.19.15` using PM2 or Node.
- **Firewall Audit**: Use PowerShell on the backend server to ensure port 5000 is open.
- **Logs Inspection**: Review Nginx error logs on the frontend server to confirm the exact upstream failure reason.

### 2. Configuration Adjustments

#### [MODIFY] [nginx-windows.conf](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/nginx-windows.conf)
If the backend and frontend are on the same server, update the `proxy_pass` to point to `localhost`.

#### [MODIFY] [server/.env](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/server/.env)
Ensure the `BACKEND_URL` and `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` are correctly set for the production environment.

### 3. Service Restart
- Restart the backend service (if it was crashed or not started).
- Reload Nginx configuration to apply any proxy changes.

## Open Questions

- **Where is the backend running?** Is it on `10.172.19.15` or `10.172.19.16`?
- **Are you using PM2?** The previous attempt to run `pm2 status` failed because it's not in the PATH. We may need to locate it or use standard `node` commands.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "http://10.172.19.16/api/health" -Method Get`: Verify Nginx proxy to backend health check.
- `browser_subagent`: Re-test login with the provided credentials (`tkymeu@gmail.com`) to ensure successful redirection to `/dashboard`.

### Manual Verification
- Manually log in via the browser and verify that the "Welcome back" toast appears.
